          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Medicare Prescription Drug Savings and Choice Act of 2015</strong> </p> <p>This bill amends part D (Voluntary Prescription Drug Benefit Program) of title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act to require the Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services (CMS) to offer one or more Medicare-operated prescription drug plan options.&nbsp; In doing so, CMS must: (1) negotiate prices&nbsp;with drug manufacturers;&nbsp;(2) establish an appeals process for denials of plan benefits, including the option for external review and determination by an independent entity; and (3) establish and apply a formulary and formulary incentives. In general, a Medicare-operated drug plan must meet the same requirements as apply to any other prescription drug plan.</p>]]></text>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <actionDate>2015-07-28</actionDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
